{{Infobox company | name = Bahrain National Gas Company | image = Bahrain National Gas Company logo.png | type = [[State-owned enterprise]] | foundation = 1979 | location = [[Southern Governorate]], [[Bahrain]] | key_people = Dr. Mohamed bin Khalifa Al Khalifa, CEO | num_employees = 500 (2010) | revenue = $282 million (2014) | industry = [[Liquefied petroleum gas|LPG]], [[naphtha]] | products = [[propane]], [[butane]], [[naphtha]] | homepage = [http://www.banagas.com.bh/ www.banagas.com.bh] }}
'''Banagas''' (formally the '''Bahrain National Gas Company''') is a [[Bahrain]]i gas company, headquartered in Bahrain's [[Southern Governorate]]. Banagas operates [[Liquefied petroleum gas|LPG]] plant facilities which recover [[propane]], [[butane]] and [[naphtha]] from the [[Bahrain Oil Field]]'s associated gas and refinery off-gas. Some 94% of the total workforce are Bahrain nationals. 75% of the company's shares are owned by the Government of Bahrain, with the remaining shares owned by [[Boubyan Petrochemical Company]] of [[Kuwait]] and [[Chevron Corporation]]'s Bahrain subsidiary, Chevron Bahrain.
==History==
The company was founded in 1979 by Shaikh [[Isa bin Salman Al Khalifa]] with the objective of utilizing Bahrain's gas resources, by processing associated gas and refinery off-gas into marketable products. The entire US$100 million project included the construction of four gas compressor stations, a processing plant to recover [[propane]], [[butane]] and [[naphtha]], and a storage area at [[Sitra]]. In 1980 the first ship to transport gas was the [[Japan]]ese tanker ''Yuyo Maru'' which was loaded with 5,000 tonnes of butane. In 1988 the total capacity of the plant was upgraded from 170 (48.1×105m³) million cubic feet/day to 280 million cubic feet/day (79.3×105m³).<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.banagas.com.bh/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=47&catid=35&Itemid=58 | title = Introduction | accessdate = August 24, 2010 | publisher = Bahrain National Gas Company | archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20100721125350/http://www.banagas.com.bh/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=47&catid=35&Itemid=58| archivedate= 21 July 2010 <!--DASHBot-->| deadurl= no}}</ref>
==Current Operations==
Banagas compresses associated gas and refinery off-gas at its compressor stations before being sent to its central gas plant. After processing the treated products are routed to tanks and analyzed then pumped via a pipeline to refrigerated storage tanks at [[Sitra]]. Currently, the company has the capacity to produce 3000 bbls of Propane, 3200 bbls of Butane and 4500 bbls of Naphtha per day.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.banagas.com.bh/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=57&catid=35&Itemid=58 | title = Our Process | accessdate = August 24, 2010 | publisher = Bahrain National Gas Company | archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20100721135027/http://www.banagas.com.bh/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=57&catid=35&Itemid=58| archivedate= 21 July 2010 <!--DASHBot-->| deadurl= no}}</ref> In addition to exporting its products, Banagas uses residue gas as fuel for its own furnaces and gas turbines, while the rest is supplied to [[Aluminium Bahrain]], Riffa Power Station, and the [[Bahrain Petroleum Company|Bapco]] Refinery.
